<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06015219 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06015219 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  PROFESSIONAL; FOOTBALL; CLUB; NEW-YORK; BRIEF  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  The New York Giants might play the NFC title game Sunday without their leadingscorer and the only player who scored against the 49ers on Dec. 3 --place-kicker Matt Bahr.;    Bahr's status for the game was in doubt Monday.Giants Coach Bill Parcells said Bahr sustained a neck injury in the thirdquarter of the Giants' 31-3 win over Chicago on Sunday.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Sports  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  GIANTS PLACE-KICKER MAY MISS 49ERS GAME  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Giants Notebook  </MEMO><TEXT>     It appeared that Bahr was knocked woozy making a tackle on a kickoff returnby Dennis Gentry. He returned late in the game to kick an extra point and kickoff, but he left the locker room wearing a neck brace.;    &quot;They are concernedabout a line in the X-ray,&quot; Parcells said.;    Doctors planned to use anothertest Monday to evaluate the injury, Parcells said. A Giants spokesman said theteam would have no statement on the test until today.;    If Bahr can't play,the Giants probably would activate Raul Allegre, whose groin injury earlierthis season created a job for Bahr.;  SIMMS UPDATE: Parcells said there wasvirtually no hope that injured quarterback Phil Simms would be able to returnif the Giants reached the Super Bowl.;    &quot;The chances are a lot less than Ithought they would be,&quot; Parcells said.;    Simms sustained a severely sprainedright foot against Buffalo on Dec. 15.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Mercury News Wire Services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  SAN JOSE MERCURY NEWS  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910115  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Tuesday  </DAY><MONTH>  January  </MONTH><PG.COL>  4C  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  221  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Tuesday January 15, 199100015219,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyr